    "notes": "25kg Beast (Trapper), swamp swimmer, #App: 1d6, Treasure: None. Mouth parts (1d6); armor 1; swim 10m/action; Morale +2. A giant parasitic worm native to swamps and other bodies of stagnant water. Upon a successful attack, the leech immediately grapples its victim. The victim may try to break the grapple on the next round, or any subsequent round, but the leech enjoys a +1 bonus to grapple throws. Each round it grapples a victim, the leech automatically causes 1d6 damage via blood drain to its opponent. (Instinct 5, Pack 5)",
